bug.short_desc: Libre office doesn't scale on HiDPI
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
I just installed f24 on 2015 Macbook pro 15" with retina and everything except of libreoffice looks gorgeous. See attached screenshot which compares google docs vs libreoffice.
I didn't tweak any gtk hdi/scaling options, since it wasn't necessary, all except of office suite simply works.rpm
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
# DEFAULT NO CHANGES AFTER INSTALL $ gsettings get org.gnome.desktop.interface scaling-factor uint32 0
[lkocman@dhcp-24-174 ~]$ xdpyinfo | grep -B 2 resolution screen #0: dimensions: 2880x1800 pixels (762x476 millimeters) resolution: 96x96 dots per inch
libreoffice-writer-5.1.5.2-3.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible:
Steps to Reproduce: 1. run libreoffice/soffice on HiDPI 2. 3.
Actual results:
some HiDPI magic makes it little better, but it still doesn't look as expected
Expected results:
LibreOffice works with HiDPI by default, with no actions needed from user. See Firefox ;-)
Additional info:
https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/HiDPI # FOR TIPS
I did try to play with following, but it does only little good. Still doesn't look as expected.
export GDK_SCALE=2 export GDK_DPI_SCALE=0.5
Created attachment 1193893 libreoffice vs gdocs on HiDPI
